sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_1121691_transtec.QueryDepartmentMembers</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>true</client_callable><description>It finds the selected department group members, and return them as a list.</description><name>QueryDepartmentMembers</name><script><![CDATA[var QueryDepartmentMembers = Class.create();
QueryDepartmentMembers.prototype = Object.extendsObject(global.AbstractAjaxProcessor, {

	// getMembers function take a variable which will add when the Advanced Reference Qual is called 
	
        getMembers: function(departmentID){
	
		var department = departmentID;
		
		// Empty list to contain the result sys_id-s
		var members = [];
		// First query through every sys_user record
		var userGR = new GlideRecord('sys_user');
		userGR.query();
		while (userGR.next()){
			
			var userName = userGR.getValue('user_name');
			
			// Second query check if the particular user is a member of any department
			var groupGR = new GlideRecord('sys_user_grmember');
			groupGR.addQuery('user.user_name', userName);
			groupGR.addQuery('group.name', department);
			groupGR.query();
			while (groupGR.next()) {
				members.push(userGR.getUniqueValue());
			}
		}
			
			// Return the list of sys_id-s
			
			return members.join(',');
		},
	
    type: 'QueryDepartmentMembers'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2024-04-30 17:25:16</sys_created_on><sys_id>9a3a098393710210266272ba2bba1081</sys_id><sys_mod_count>42</sys_mod_count><sys_name>QueryDepartmentMembers</sys_name><sys_package display_value="TransTech" source="x_1121691_transtec">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="TransTech">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_9a3a098393710210266272ba2bba1081</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2024-07-25 08:03:49</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_1121691_transtec.CheckUserPosition</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>true</client_callable><description>It returns a string including the user's postion (dispatcher or driver).</description><name>CheckUserPosition</name><script><![CDATA[var CheckUserPosition = Class.create();
CheckUserPosition.prototype = Object.extendsObject(global.AbstractAjaxProcessor, {
	
	// creating the call back function for the client side script
	getUserID: function(){
		
		// declare a variable to contain the user's name from the Client Script
		var userID = this.getParameter('sysparm_userID');
		
		// list of the group names
		var groups = ['Dispatchers', 'Drivers'];
		
		// for loop to iterate the query with the number if groups
		for(var i=0; i<=1; i++){
		
			// query through the Group table to decide that the user member any of the groups 
			var groupGR = new GlideRecord('sys_user_grmember');
			groupGR.addQuery('user.user_name', userID);
			groupGR.addQuery('group.name', groups[i]);
			groupGR.query();
			if(groupGR.next()){
	
			// if the user is a member of any of the groups return the group name as a string
				if(i == 0){
					return 'dispatcher';
				}else if (i == 1){
					return 'driver';
				}
			}
		}
	},
	
    type: 'CheckUserPosition'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2024-04-28 08:45:56</sys_created_on><sys_id>07bd205293b18210266272ba2bba109a</sys_id><sys_mod_count>21</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CheckUserPosition</sys_name><sys_package display_value="TransTech" source="x_1121691_transtec">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="TransTech">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_07bd205293b18210266272ba2bba109a</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2024-07-25 11:48:18</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="DELETE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_1121691_transtec_vehicles</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition table="x_1121691_transtec_vehicles">registration_numberISNOTEMPTY^EQ<item endquery="false" field="registration_number" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="ISNOTEMPTY" or="false" value=""/><item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="=" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Registration number format</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/ ) {

    // Add your code here
    // Use JavaScript coercion to guarantee regNumber is a string and the included letters are upper case

    var regNumber = current.getValue('registration_number').toUpperCase();

    //Examine every character of regNumber with conditions and loops
    var isCorrect = false;
    //The first two letter is checked by a simple if condition
    if (regNumber[0] >= "A" && regNumber[0] <= "Z") {
        if (regNumber[1] >= "A" && regNumber[1] <= "Z") {

            //Check the last four characters of the string with a loop to ensure they are numbers
            for (var i = 2; i < 6; i++) {
                if (regNumber[i] >= '0' && regNumber[i] <= '9') {		
                    if(regNumber.length == 6){
					isCorrect = true;
					}
				} else {
                    isCorrect = false;
                    break;
                }
            }

        } else {
            isCorrect = false;
        }
    } else {
        isCorrect = false;
    }

    // If the characters of regNumber are correct type and they are in the right order,
    // set the value of the registration number to regNumber variable to ensure the 
    // letters will be saved upper cased
    if (isCorrect) {
        current.setValue('registration_number', regNumber);

        // If the string have not entered in the right format log an error message and abort the record saving
    } else {
        current.setAbortAction(true);
        gs.addErrorMessage('The registration number format must be: AA0000!');
    }
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2024-06-03 18:11:03</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>902b500e93220210266272ba2bba1039</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Registration number format</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="TransTech" source="x_1121691_transtec">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="TransTech">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_902b500e93220210266272ba2bba1039</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2024-06-03 18:11:03</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=902b500e93220210266272ba2bba1039"/></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_1121691_transtec_vehicles</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition table="x_1121691_transtec_vehicles">registration_numberISNOTEMPTY^EQ<item endquery="false" field="registration_number" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="ISNOTEMPTY" or="false" value=""/><item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="=" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Registration number format</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/ ) {

    // Add your code here
    // Use JavaScript coercion to guarantee regNumber is a string and the included letters are upper case

    var regNumber = current.getValue('registration_number').toUpperCase();

    //Examine every character of regNumber with conditions and loops
    var isCorrect = false;
    //The first two letter is checked by a simple if condition
    if (regNumber[0] >= "A" && regNumber[0] <= "Z") {
        if (regNumber[1] >= "A" && regNumber[1] <= "Z") {

            //Check the last four characters of the string with a loop to ensure they are numbers
            for (var i = 2; i < 6; i++) {
                if (regNumber[i] >= '0' && regNumber[i] <= '9') {		
                    if(regNumber.length == 6){
					isCorrect = true;
					}
				} else {
                    isCorrect = false;
                    break;
                }
            }

        } else {
            isCorrect = false;
        }
    } else {
        isCorrect = false;
    }

    // If the characters of regNumber are correct type and they are in the right order,
    // set the value of the registration number to regNumber variable to ensure the 
    // letters will be saved upper cased
    if (isCorrect) {
        current.setValue('registration_number', regNumber);

        // If the string have not entered in the right format log an error message and abort the record saving
    } else {
        current.setAbortAction(true);
        gs.addErrorMessage('The registration number format must be: AA0000!');
    }
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2024-04-27 07:58:16</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>204e93b593fd0210266272ba2bba10b2</sys_id><sys_mod_count>21</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Registration number format</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="TransTech" source="x_1121691_transtec">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="TransTech">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_204e93b593fd0210266272ba2bba10b2</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2024-06-03 18:04:40</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=204e93b593fd0210266272ba2bba10b2"/></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="DELETE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_1121691_transtec.QueryDepartmentMembers</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>true</client_callable><description>This Script Include has two queries, the first iterate through the sys_user table, and the second query find the departmen group members, and return it as a list.</description><name>QueryDepartmentMembers</name><script><![CDATA[var QueryDepartmentMembers = Class.create();
QueryDepartmentMembers.prototype = {
        initialize: function() {},
		
		// getMembers function take a variable which will add when the Advanced Reference Qual is called 
        getMembers: function (department){
		
		// Empty list to contain the result sys_id-s
		var members = [];
		
		// First query through every sys_user record
		var userGR = new GlideRecord('sys_user');
		userGR.query();
		while (userGR.next()){
			
			var userName = userGR.getValue('user_name');
			
			// Second query check if the particular user is a member of any department
			var groupGR = new GlideRecord('sys_user_grmember');
			groupGR.addQuery('user.user_name', userName);
			groupGR.addQuery('group.name', department);
			groupGR.query();
			while (groupGR.next()) {
				members.push(userGR.getUniqueValue());
			}
		}
			
			// Return the list included the sys_id-s
			return members;
			
		},
            type: 'QueryDepartmentMembers'
        };]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2024-04-29 19:49:30</sys_created_on><sys_id>da2c543e937dc210266272ba2bba109c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count><sys_name>QueryDepartmentMembers</sys_name><sys_package display_value="TransTech" source="x_1121691_transtec">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="TransTech">5716efc693254210266272ba2bba1064</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_da2c543e937dc210266272ba2bba109c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2024-04-29 20:03:50</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>
